@startuml C4_Concern_DistributedConsistency
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Cross-Cutting Concern - Distributed Consistency

Boundary(consistency_models, "Consistency Models") {
    Component(acid, "ACID Transactions", "Guarantee", "Single-node only")
    Component(eventual, "Eventual Consistency", "Guarantee", "Multi-node async")
    Component(strong_eventual, "Strong Eventual", "Guarantee", "Eventual + conflict-free")
}

Boundary(sync_strategy, "Synchronization Strategy") {
    Component(pessimistic, "Pessimistic Locking", "Strategy", "Lock before write")
    Component(optimistic, "Optimistic Locking", "Strategy", "Detect conflicts")
    Component(event_sourcing, "Event Sourcing", "Strategy", "Immutable log")
}

Boundary(conflict_resolution, "Conflict Resolution") {
    Component(last_write_wins, "LastWriteWins", "Simple", "Latest timestamp")
    Component(vector_clock, "VectorClock", "Causal", "Ordering by causality")
    Component(crdt, "CRDT", "Conflict-Free", "Commutative operations")
}

Boundary(replication, "Replication Model") {
    Component(sync_repl, "SynchronousReplication", "Consistency", "Wait for all")
    Component(async_repl, "AsynchronousReplication", "Performance", "Fire and forget")
    Component(semi_sync, "Semi-SynchronousReplication", "Hybrid", "Wait for quorum")
}

Boundary(examples, "Example Scenarios") {
    Component(bank_transfer, "BankTransfer", "ACID", "Must use transactions")
    Component(user_profile, "UserProfile", "Eventual", "Cache allowed")
    Component(shopping_cart, "ShoppingCart", "Eventual", "OK to be stale")
}

consistency_models --> sync_strategy: Informs
sync_strategy --> conflict_resolution: Uses
replication --> consistency_models: Achieves

Note as N1
Consistency Models Trade-offs:

ACID (Strong):
- Consistency: Perfect
- Availability: Lower
- Partition: Not tolerated
- Use: Financial transactions

Eventual (Weak):
- Consistency: Delayed
- Availability: High
- Partition: Tolerated
- Use: User profiles, caches

Strong Eventual (Best of Both):
- Consistency: Eventually consistent + commutative
- Availability: High
- Partition: Tolerated
- Use: Distributed databases (CRDTs)

CAP Theorem: Pick 2 of 3
- Consistency: All reads see latest write
- Availability: System always responds
- Partition tolerance: Works despite network splits

YAWL Strategy:
- Workflow state: Semi-sync replication (safety)
- Cache data: Async replication (speed)
- Event log: Sync replication (audit trail)
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
